Description:
Premium Living on a Corner Block in a Central Location.
Light, bright and inviting, updated with style and located in one of the most popular suburbs in Geelong this substantial 3 bedroom home set on a corner allotment of app. 532 sqm. will appeal to any genuine buyer searching for a home that offers it all at a very affordable price.
Theres literally nothing more to do other than plan where to put your furniture with outstanding updates including fully equipped kitchen with stainless steel cooker, range hood and dishwasher, exquisite light fittings, polished floor boards right throughout the home and a well appointed central bathroom with separate shower and bath.
The intelligently designed open plan living, dining and kitchen area is the ideal place to entertain family and friends with reverse cycle heating and cooling unit, ceiling fan and heavy blinds for all year round comfort and privacy while theres also a fantastic outdoor entertainment area overlooking the spacious rear yard for those that love to make the most of those long Summer afternoons. The corner allotment also means theres plenty of space for a boat, caravan or trailer plus plenty of off street parking for multiple vehicles in the 2 car garage and wide driveway.
Within walking distance to local schools, 2 shopping centres and East Geelong Gordon TAFE campus this outstanding home sells itself on location alone and for those that require public transport theres easy access to busses that will take you to all that Geelong and has to offer stress free and within minutes from leaving your home. This really is one not to be missed; take the time and make it yours!
App. Rental $380 per week.

Description:
Your Own Piece of the Leafy East
This charming home nestled amongst beautiful gardens is set on a generous 693sqm (approx.) corner block in one of the most favoured pockets of East Geelong.
Offering a well-designed floor plan, large north-facing windows in the open living/kitchen/dining area bring in an abundance of natural light and frame beautiful views of the established gardens. Bi-fold windows open up across the length of the kitchen to the outdoor entertaining area which is situated centrally, providing a protected and easily accessible space for alfresco dining.
Comprising four bedrooms, all with BIRs, two bathrooms, two living areas plus outdoor entertaining area, single garage and double carport, this is a well-appointed home that provides a spacious central hub, with separate zones to accommodate family lifestyle.
Other features include ducted evaporative cooling, updated kitchen with stone bench tops and a modern central bathroom with double shower and double vanity.
Located only a short stroll to the Eastern Gardens and within minutes of the Waterfront, shopping, cafes, the Geelong Hospital and CBD; the proximity to attractions and amenities is hard to beat. And whilst the location is central, the home itself creates a feeling of sanctuary by bringing the outdoors in and making the beautiful surrounding greenery part of your everyday living. You can have the best of both worlds here!
Terms: 10% Deposit, 60 day Settlement. For alternative arrangements, please discuss with agent.

Description:
Huge opportunity.
Sale by SET DATE 25/9/2019 (unless sold prior)
Rarely does an opportunity to purchase such a large property in the heart of Newcomb present itself but here it is, a 4 bedroom home on a huge potential development site (STCA) on 2380m2 (approx.) block. This much loved home consisting of 4 large bedrooms all with built in robes and master with ensuite. Large L shaped lounge room and meals area leading into the good sized fully appointed kitchen and large walk in pantry. Complete with formal dining room and a large study and a huge fully covered outdoor alfresco area for the largest of families entertaining parties and BBQs. With plenty of garaging and shedding to accommodate up to 6 cars or would suit a tradie with plenty of storage space. The massive backyard area would be a dream for the kids to play in with those summer cricket games or for those large pets to roam around the property. This property lends itself to plenty of opportunities for the largest of families or for the astute developer (STCA). Located just minutes from Newcomb & Bellarine shopping centres, primary and secondary schools, Gordan Tafe and less than 10 minutes from Geelong's CBD and waterfront. The property is zoned General Residential Zone -Schedule 1 (GRZ1).

Description:
Here is a real charmer
With stylish and tasteful renovations throughout, this home is one that is sure to impress. Comprising a spacious light filled open plan kitchen/dining/family area with gas heater and reverse cycle air conditioner. The kitchen has gorgeous stone benchtops, induction cooktop and electric fan forced oven, dishwasher, mirrored splashbacks and a walk in butler's pantry.
The 3 bedrooms are all a good size and conveniently located near the central bathroom with floor to ceiling tiling, modern vanity, frameless shower, heated flooring and a separate toilet.
Outdoors is ideal for the entertainer with a decked area, undercover entertaining and a compact inground pool. The side drive leads to a carport for off street parking and a garage which has been converted to a rumpus room, perfect for teenagers to have their own space. The north facing allotment is approximately 604 sqm.
All this is walking distance to local shops, schools, public transport, sporting reserves and 10 minutes to Geelong CBD, the Waterfront and the Bellarine. Suiting both owner occupiers and investors, with a potential rental income of $420 per week, this is one to put high on your inspection list.

Description:
Large family home, great location.
Here is an opportunity to secure something as unique as this 3 bedroom brick veneer family home located right in the heart of Newcomb. From the moment you enter the property you will be amazed at the size of the rooms and with 9ft ceilings throughout, this property lends itself to an array of opportunities to simply invest, move in or make an amazing transformation for those with the inspiration. The huge 5m x 4.3m master bedroom and bedrooms 2 & 3, both expansive rooms, can cater for the larger families or for those with plenty of room to grow. Good sized bathroom, large laundry and a spacious kitchen and lounge room with air conditioning and ducted heating throughout the home, this home has it all. Complete with a single car garage and plenty of space in the large backyard, which includes fruit trees, and still has plenty of room for entertaining or for the kids to play. Located just minutes from Newcomb Central & Bellarine Village Shopping Centres, schools, public transport, Gordon Tafe, less than 10 minutes to Geelong CBD and waterfront and 30 minutes from Geelong's best beaches. This is an opportunity not to be missed, get into the thriving Newcomb market and make this your new family home or a great opportunity to add to your property portfolio.

Description:
When location counts
Situated in undoubtedly one of the best streets in East Geelong, this location is sure to attract a lot of attention. Walking distance to the Botanical gardens, the Waterfront, local shops and cafes and only a few minutes from Geelong CBD, the convenience is sure to suit both owner occupiers and savvy investors, with a potential rental income of $400/wk.
Built in 2013, this quality built property offers low maintenance living without compromising on living space. Comprising a light filled open plan kitchen/dining/family with stunning floorboards throughout and split system AC. The kitchen has stone bench tops, plenty of cupboard and bench space, a 900mm s/s freestanding stove and dishwasher. The dining area opens out to a very private decked entertaining area with mains gas available for the barbeque and plumbing ready to go if you require a kitchenette/sink.
Downstairs is the laundry and a powder room. Upstairs are two spacious bedrooms each with built in robes, ceiling fans, high loft style ceilings and split system airconditioners for all year comfort. The main bathroom provides a modern vanity, separate bath and shower and separate toilet. At the top of the stairwell is the perfect spot for a study nook.
The single garage is remote controlled and has internal access to the home. The extra length provides plenty of room for storage.
Make your enquiries today, this home is sure to attract a lot of attention for the position alone.

Location, Style and Sophistication!

Frederick Street remains one of the most highly regarded and exclusive streets in East Geelong just one of the many reasons to be excited about this opportunity. The picture-perfect presentation of this modern masterpiece will immediately strike a chord among those searching for a brand-new quality home in a classic family setting. Add to the mix on-trend technology and sophisticated design in an iconic family-friendly location that's within walking distance to the Botanical Gardens, Waterfront, Garden Street Café Precinct, CBD and easy access to the Bellarine Peninsula, you'll be hard-pressed to find a better setting.
Tasteful styling divided across two levels creates a luxurious environment inviting you into a spacious master bedroom downstairs with customised WIR and ensuite. As you follow the hardwood floors past the powder room through to the central hub of the home, you are greeted by a light filled open plan living area graced with high ceilings and a fully equipped gourmet kitchen with walk-in party, stone bench tops and Bosch appliances, perfect for the master chef of the house. The gas log fire creates a sense of intimacy as you dine with friends and loved ones. Walk up the custom-built staircase where a further three large bedrooms reside accompanied by a chic bathroom with oval standalone bathtub perfect for the growing family or where your guests will feel quite special. A second north facing, large living room with study nook that could easily double as a media room adds to the versatile floor plan with partial views of the Botanical Gardens. Indoor / outdoor alfresco entertaining off the main living zone downstairs is perfect for all occasions accompanied by low maintenance manicured gardens and an oversized SLUG with internal access and additional off-street car parking.
With no expense spared, additional features include a 6.1 star energy rating, ducted reverse cycle heating and cooling with phone app connectivity, double glazed argon-filled Rylock windows, solar hot water with gas boosting, ducted vacuum, security and intercom, USB power points, pyrolytic self clean oven, induction cook top and integrated dishwasher are all included for your enjoyment. Standing proudly amongst distinguished domains in Easts finest belt, this tightly-held tree lined street provides the perfect backdrop for an exceptionally rare opportunity to create an enviable lifestyle.
